### What problem does this feature solve?
Currently, you need to preserve locally the callback used in $on to propertly clean the event handler in view destroyed.

This is inconvenient if you dont want to save/expose the handler and prefer to use anonymous handler function.

```
    function onSidebarSaveEvent(){ /* this... */ }
    export default {
        created() {
            this.$root.$on("params-edit-sidebar-save", (arg) => {
                onSidebarSaveEvent.call(this);
            });
        }
		destroyed() {
			this.$off("params-edit-sidebar-save", /* no handle to unbind? */)
        },
}
```

I propose to pick the same convention jquery used for on()/off() - event names are namespaced so you can give the event handler name and unbind this specific name. 

on("click.thatNamespace") / off("click.thatNamespace")

the $emit("click") still triggers all on("click.*")  handlers. multiple namespaces are supported. http://api.jquery.com/on/#event-names


The choice of namespace separator is arbitrary - can use dot(already used by modifiers?) or colon.

### What does the proposed API look like?
Vue.prototype.$emit("event") to emit an event - no changes

Vue.prototype.$on("event:namespace") to attached namespaced handler. namespaces are optional, multiple allowed?.

Vue.prototype.$off("event:namespace") to remove namespaced handler (no explicit handler mention is required)

